 Popular Nigerian on-air personality, Osi Suave, has shared his opinion on the way society holds women to a higher standard than men. The media personality used popular Nigerian singer and songwriter, Tiwa Savage and BBNaija Shine Ya Eye season 6 former finalist, Cross as the case study for his argument. “Person preek dey Snapchat and we all moved on like nothing. But we were dropping think pieces on Tiwa’s tape. I think we are all hypocrites tbh cos it beats me how we hold women to a higher moral standard than men,” the OAP said via his Twitter account. Read Also: OAP Osi Suave Wants To Be A Lady In His Next Life (Photo)